<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=2 -->
On January 27, 1992, Learjet Inc. (Lear), 8220 West Harry Street, Wichita, KS 67209&hyph;2942, P.O. Box 7707, Wichita,
KS 67277&hyph;7707, applied for a new type certificate in the transport airplane category for the Model 45 airplane.
The Learjet Model 45 is a T-tail, low wing, medium sized business jet powered by two Garrett TFE 731&hyph;20 turbofan
engines mounted on pylons extending from the aft fuselage. Each engine will be capable of delivering 3,500 lbs. thrust
(3,650 lbs. thrust with auto performance reserve). The airplane will be capable of operating with two flight crewmembers
and a maximum of ten passengers (standard is eight passengers).
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

