<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
EPA believes the proposed part 59 procedures faithfully 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
implement Congressional intent for the field citation program, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and satisfy procedural due process concerns. This belief is 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
bolstered by judicial acceptance of similar procedures in a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
variety of related situations. See Chemical Waste Management, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Inc. (court upheld EPA's non-APA hearing procedures for issuance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of administrative orders concerning corrective action orders 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section 3008(h) of RCRA); 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
United States
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 v. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Independent Bulk 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Transport, Inc.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
, 480 F. Supp. 474 (S.D. NY 1979) (court upheld 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
non-APA hearing held by Coast Guard in assessing less than the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
maximum $5,000 civil penalty per unlawful discharge under the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal Water Pollution Control Act). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
H. Design of Field Citations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Field citations will be of a standardized format nationwide, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
and will be issued in triplicate. The following information 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall be included on the field citation: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Date and time of violation(s); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Inspector's name, title, and office; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Name and address of source; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Name and telephone number of owner/operator or his/her 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
representative; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Specific violation(s); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) Location/source/description of violation(s); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) Proposed penalty; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) Notification of the 30-day deadline to either pay the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
penalty or request a hearing; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(9) Address to which payment must be sent; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(10) Address to which a request for a hearing must be sent; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(11) Inspector's signature; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(12) Space for signature indicating receipt; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(13) Citation number. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
The actual format of the citation will be published in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Agency's guidance document. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
V. Section-by-Section Analysis 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
A. Section 59.1&blank;Purpose and Scope 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section of the proposed rule states EPA's authority to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
develop a field citation program and explains that procedures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
developed in this part will be used in administering the field 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
citation program. The section acknowledges the twin goals of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
field citation program: ensuring compliance with the Act and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
providing for expedited enforcement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
B. Section 59.2&blank;Use of Number and Gender 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section clarifies that words in the singular also 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
include the plural, and those in the masculine gender also 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
include the feminine, and vice versa. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
C. Section 59.3&blank;Computation of Time 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section provides that any time period specified in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
these rules shall begin the day following the event from which 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the period begins, and shall include Saturdays, Sundays, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Federal legal holidays. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
D. Section 59.4&blank;Definitions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section provides definitions of terms used in part 59. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
E. Section 59.5&blank;Determination of Minor Violation and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Maximum Proposed Penalty 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section describes the process that will be used to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determine whether a violation is minor. Each violation will be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
evaluated according to the proposed list of factors provided. A 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
violation will be determined as minor through evaluation of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
factors, considered as a whole. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Criminal violations will not be addressed under the field 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
citations program. Criminal enforcement action may be pursued 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for the violations described in section 113(c). These violations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
include ``knowing'' violations such as knowing endangerment, in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
which a person knowingly releases a hazardous air pollutant, with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the knowledge that the release is placing another person in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
imminent danger of death or serious bodily injury. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
This section also provides the proposed maximum civil 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
penalty for a minor violation as $5,000 per day of violation, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
defines a field citation's total proposed penalty as the sum of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
each individual minor violation's proposed penalty. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpart B_Rules Governing Hearings on Field Citations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
F. Section 59.6&blank;Scope of These Rules 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section outlines the purpose of Subpart B, which is to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
establish streamlined administrative procedures for conducting 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
hearings under section &sect;113(d)(3) of the Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
G. Section 59.7&blank;Issuance and Service of Field Citations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
This section describes who may issue field citations and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
what should be contained therein. The section also details 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements for service of a field citation. The statute limits 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the authority to issue field citations to EPA officers or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
employees. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

