<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Issue subpoenas pursuant to &sect;59.17 for the attendance and testimony of witnesses and for the production
of relevant information and documents. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Issue or modify a prehearing order pursuant to &sect;59.15(c); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Schedule and further limit the information exchange pursuant to &sect;59.16; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Impose sanctions pursuant to &sect;59.16 or to aid in the maintenance of order and the efficient and impartial
administration of justice; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Certify the administrative record and set forth and transmit a recommended decision pursuant to &sect;59.22.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Presiding Officer shall, in a timely fashion: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
