<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(1) Carry out his duties as required by this part;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Oversee and direct the activities of the Hearing Clerk in an action under this part;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Schedule activities of the parties pursuant to the requirements of this part; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Take any other action necessary for the maintenance of order and for the efficient and impartial adjudication
of allegations arising in an action under this part.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The Presiding Officer shall not:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Have any prior connection with the action before him, including the performance or supervision of investigative
or prosecutorial functions;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Have any interest in the outcome of the action;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Grant an extension, delay or continuance to a party based on a party's request for information pursuant to law outside
the scope of this part;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Allow the introduction of any document or testimony into the administrative record relating to settlement of
the instant action; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Dismiss the field citation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.9
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Hearing clerk.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Regional Administrator shall designate a Hearing Clerk. After the filing of a field citation by the Complainant
with the Regional Hearing Clerk, the Hearing Clerk shall:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(a) Timely notify each party in writing of the name of the Presiding Officer designated to preside over the case;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) Record the date of receipt of each document received regarding the action;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) Timely notify the Presiding Officer of the receipt of any document filed with the Clerk by either party;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Perform such other functions as required by the Presiding Officer to assist him in carrying out his responsibilities
under this part; and
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) Perform such ministerial and clerical functions as required by the Regional Administrator or by the Environmental
Appeals Board to assist each in carrying out its responsibilities under this part.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.10
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Representation by counsel.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The respondent has the right to be represented at all stages of the proceedings by counsel. Following notification
that a respondent is represented by counsel, all further communications regarding the proceedings shall be directed
to that counsel.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.11
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Preliminary matters.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Within 30 days after receipt of the field citation, the respondent, or counsel for the respondent, may:
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Request a hearing;
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Provide any written evidence and arguments in lieu of a hearing; or
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Pay the penalty proposed in the citation. A hearing must be requested in writing and must specify the issues which
are in dispute. Any request for hearing shall be filed with the Hearing Clerk.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The right to a hearing is waived if the respondent fails to submit the request to the Hearing Clerk within thirty
(30) days after service of the field citation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) If the respondent fails to respond to the field citation in accordance with the provisions of this section, the
penalty proposed in the field citation shall be final and immediately payable. The Agency shall file with the Hearing
Clerk, no later than ten (10) days following the respondent's failure to respond, a written explanation supporting
the penalty amount requested by the field citation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) The Presiding Officer shall promptly schedule all hearings. The Presiding Officer shall grant such delays or
continuances as may be necessary or desirable in the interest of fairly resolving the case.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The respondent may amend the response no later than ten (10) days prior to the scheduled hearing date. Issues raised
later than ten (10) days before the scheduled hearing may be presented only at the discretion of the Presiding Officer.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.12
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Revocation of field citation.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
At any time before the penalty proposed by the field citation becomes final, the Complainant may revoke the field citation,
in whole or in part, without prejudice.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.13
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Request for confidential treatment. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
