<DOCNO> FR940503-1-00050 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940503-1-00010 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) A request for confidential treatment of a document or portion thereof may be made by the respondent on the basis
that the information is: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Confidential financial information, trade secrets, or other material exempt from disclosure by the Freedom
of Information Act (5 U.S.C. 552); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Required to be held in confidence by 18 U.S.C. 1905; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Otherwise exempt by law from disclosure. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The respondent must submit the request for confidential treatment to the Presiding Officer in writing and must
state the reasons justifying nondisclosure. Failure to make a timely request may result in a document being considered
as nonconfidential and subject to release. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.14 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Consent agreements and consent orders. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) At any time before final Agency action, the complainant and the respondent may settle an action, in whole or in part,
by agreeing upon a civil penalty, with or without conditions. The parties shall memorialize such an agreement in the
form of a consent agreement. The Presiding Officer shall thereafter enter a consent order in accordance with the terms
of the consent agreement. Such consent order may not be appealed to federal court by either party. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) If the filing of the consent order with the Hearing Clerk pursuant to paragraph (a) of this section does not wholly
conclude the action, the Presiding Officer shall promptly inform the parties of the schedule of the remaining proceedings.

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.15 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Prehearing conference. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Within thirty (30) days following receipt of the respondent's response to the field citation, the Presiding Officer
may, in his discretion, hold a prehearing conference. The Presiding Officer may conduct the conference in person
or by telephone. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) At the prehearing conference, the Presiding Officer: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) May attempt to simplify issues and assist the parties in reaching a stipulation as to facts that are not in dispute;

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) May, upon request of either party, schedule an exchange of information in accordance with &sect;59.16; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Shall establish a time and place for the hearing; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) May discuss other appropriate matters. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The Presiding Officer may issue a prehearing order to the parties, no later than twenty (20) days following the
conference, which memorializes the rulings of the Presiding Officer made at the prehearing conference. 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.16 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Information exchange. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Subject to any limitation imposed by the Presiding Officer in a prehearing order issued pursuant to &sect;59.15(c)
each party shall provide, in writing, the following information: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The name of each witness it intends to present at the hearing and the subject matter of the intended testimony; and

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Each document it intends to introduce at the hearing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The respondent shall provide the following information in writing, to the Agency: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) If the respondent contends that it is unable to pay the proposed penalty, the respondent shall submit financial
information in support of such claim, including, but not limited to, complete copies of its federal income tax returns
for the previous three years; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The respondent's net profits, delayed or avoided costs, or any other form of economic benefit resulting from any
activity or failure to act by the respondent which is alleged in the field citation; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The respondent's good faith efforts to comply with the applicable Clean Air Act requirements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The parties shall conduct the exchange of information according to the schedule established by the Presiding
Officer pursuant to &sect;59.15(c). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) Each party shall file its information exchange with the Hearing Clerk and shall simultaneously serve copies thereof
personally or by certified mail (or any other manner of service that is no less speedy and reliable), with an attached
certificate of service, upon the other party and the Presiding Officer. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The Presiding Officer has the discretion to impose on any party that fails to comply with the requirements of this
section any sanction that is just and proper.
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940503-1-00051 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940503-1-00010 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.17 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Subpoenas. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Presiding Officer may, on his own initiative or at 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the request of either party, subpoena the testimony of witnesses 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or the production of documents, or both, for a hearing conducted 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
pursuant to &sect;59.16. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Presiding Officer shall serve the subpoena upon its 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
recipient in the manner prescribed for the service of a field 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
citation pursuant to &sect;59.7(d). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) The Presiding Officer shall file a copy of the subpoena 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with the Hearing Clerk. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.18 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Hearing procedures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Presiding Officer shall conduct a fair and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
impartial proceeding in which each party has a reasonable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
opportunity to be heard and to present evidence. Each witness 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
shall testify in the form determined by the Presiding Officer to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be most efficient in resolving an issue. Forms of testimony 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
include oral testimony provided in person or by other means, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
written or otherwise recorded testimony. The Presiding Officer 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
may limit the number of witnesses and the scope and extent of any 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
direct examination or cross-examination as necessary to protect 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the interests of justice and conduct a reasonably expeditious 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
hearing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Agency representative shall present the field 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
citation and the evidence supporting its issuance, and any other 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
material that is pertinent to the issues to be determined by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Presiding Officer. The respondent has the right to examine, and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to respond to or rebut, the field citation and any proffered 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
evidence and material. The respondent may offer any facts, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
documents, testimony or other exculpatory evidence which bears on 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
appropriate issues, or which may be relevant to the size of an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
appropriate penalty. Any opposing party has a right of crossexamination after the introduction of a witness' direct

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
testimony. A party shall not cross-examine regarding a matter 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that is outside of the scope of the direct examination. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Presiding Officer may require the authentication of any written 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
exhibit or statement. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(c) At the close of the respondent's presentation of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
evidence, the Presiding Officer may allow the introduction of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
rebuttal evidence by the Agency representative. The Presiding 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Officer may allow the respondent to respond to any such evidence 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
submitted by the Agency. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(d) In receiving evidence, the Presiding Officer is not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
bound by the Federal Rules of Evidence. In evaluating the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
evidence presented, the Presiding Officer shall give due 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consideration to the reliability and relevance of each item of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
evidence. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(e) The Presiding Officer may take notice of matters which 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
are not subject to reasonable dispute and are commonly known in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the community, or are capable of accurate and ready determination 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
by resort to sources whose accuracy cannot reasonably be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
questioned. Prior to taking notice of a matter, the Presiding 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Officer shall give each party an opportunity to show why notice 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
should not be taken. In any case in which notice is taken, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Presiding Officer shall place in the record a written statement 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the matter as to which notice was taken with the basis for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
such notice, including either a statement that the parties 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consented to notice being taken or a summary of any party's 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
objections. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.19 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Penalty assessment criteria. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The Presiding Officer shall consider the following 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
criteria in reviewing the penalty proposed in the field citation: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) The size of the business; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) The economic impact of the penalty on the business; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) The respondent's full compliance history, and good faith 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
efforts by the respondent to comply; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) The duration of the violation as established by any 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
credible evidence (including evidence other than the applicable 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
test method); 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(5) Payment by the respondent of penalties previously 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
assessed for the same violation; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(6) The economic benefit of noncompliance; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(7) The seriousness of the violation; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(8) Such other factors as justice may require. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The burden of going forward with respect to criteria in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
paragraphs (a)(1), (2), (3), (5), and (6) of this section, is on 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the respondent. The burden of going forward with respect to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
criteria in paragraphs (a)(4) and (7) of this section is on the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Agency. The burden of going forward with respect to criterion in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
paragraph (a)(8) of this section is on the party proffering such 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
factors. Failure of the respondent to meet its burden with 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
respect to any applicable criterion shall mean that a penalty 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amount that is appropriate in light of other criteria shall also 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be appropriate in light of such criterion for which the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
respondent failed to meet its burden. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.20 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Transcript or recording of hearing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) The hearing shall be tape recorded unless the parties 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
agree and the Presiding Officer directs otherwise. A verbatim 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
transcript will not normally be prepared, but may be ordered by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Presiding Officer if deemed necessary to permit a full and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
fair review and resolution of the case. If not so ordered by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Presiding Officer, a party may, at its own expense, cause a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
verbatim transcript to be made. The party causing the verbatim 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
transcript to be made shall submit one (1) copy to the Presiding 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Officer and one (1) copy to the other party. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The transcript or recording of the hearing, together 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with all written submissions made by the parties, shall become 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
part of the administrative record for the proceeding. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.21 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Post-hearing submissions. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The Presiding Officer may request, within a reasonable time 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
following the conclusion of the hearing, that the parties submit 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a written statement for his consideration including, but not 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
limited to, proposed recommended findings of fact and conclusions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of law. Such written statement shall be limited to the matters 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
raised at the hearing. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=80 g=1 f=1 -->
&sect;59.22 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=89 g=1 f=1 -->
Recommended decision. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
(a) Within a reasonable time after the conclusion of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
hearing, the Presiding Officer shall: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Certify the administrative record as complete; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Make the administrative record available to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Regional Administrator; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Prepare and transmit a recommended decision to the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Regional Administrator. The recommended decision shall address 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
all material issues of fact or law properly raised by the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
respondent, and shall recommend that the field citation be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
affirmed, modified or withdrawn. The recommended decision shall 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be based on substantial evidence in the administrative record, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
taken as a whole, and shall provide citations to relevant 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
material contained in that record. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(b) The Presiding Officer shall file a copy of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
recommended decision with the Hearing Clerk at the time of its 
