<PARENT> FR940503-1-00011 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
D. Confidentiality 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Because today's proposal contemplates the EPA receiving and using information and services from private sources
for enforcement activities, the EPA is also proposing to maintain as confidential, upon request, the identity of
persons providing information or services. The EPA believes this assurance of confidentiality will encourage persons
to assist the EPA in its efforts to enforce compliance with the Act. In this regard, the proposed rule provides, upon
request, confidential treatment by the EPA consistent with this proposal, existing law and other EPA regulations.
Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act (FOIA), 5 U.S.C. 552 (b)(6) &amp; (7), the confidentiality of the identity
of those providing information and services will be protected from FOIA requests consistent with existing law. The
assurance of confidentiality extends to petitions for awards submitted to the EPA. To ensure confidential treatment
of such petitions, it is important that persons submitting petitions to the EPA specifically request confidentiality
at or prior to the time of providing information or services, and to renew such request at the time of submitting a petition.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
E. Petitions for Awards 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Because the information or services provided would be instrumental to the successful prosecution of the EPA's enforcement
action, in many cases EPA personnel will be aware of persons potentially eligible for an award, even without a petition
being submitted. The EPA expects that in many such situations, award determinations may be made without submission
of a petition. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Today's proposal recognizes, however, that a person may wish to petition the Agency for consideration for an award
and authorizes such petitions. To ensure that such petitions contain sufficient information for the purpose of evaluation,
and to ensure that petitions are directed to the appropriate EPA office, the proposal sets forth award petition procedures
and requirements. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
Timing of Petitions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The proposed rule requires petitions for consideration to be submitted in writing no later than one year after the
judgment of conviction or assessment of a civil penalty. Petitions may be submitted at any time prior to the judgment
or assessment, but no award determination will be made before the judgment of conviction is entered or a judicial or
administrative civil penalty is finally assessed, agreed, or ordered. Again, payment and the amount of any award
granted is within the Administrator's unfettered discretion. The granting of an award is a gratuity, and not an entitlement.

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
Certification of Eligibility 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The proposed regulation also requires that the petition contain a certification of compliance with the eligibility
criteria set forth in the regulation. A statement signed by the person to be considered for an award attesting to having
read the eligibility requirements and attesting that the person to be considered for an award is not ineligible to
receive an award would meet this requirement. This certification is important to the award determination process
because the EPA recognizes that it may be difficult for the Administrator to determine with certainty whether a person
meets all eligibility criteria. However, the Act prohibits payment of an award to certain persons. Therefore, the
proposal requires a certification of eligibility be signed before the Administrator may pay an award. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG /STAG -->
</TEXT>
</DOC>



<DOC>
<DOCNO> FR940503-1-00056 </DOCNO>
<PARENT> FR940503-1-00011 </PARENT>
<TEXT>
 
<!-- PJG STAG 4702 -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
F. Criteria for Awards 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Under the Act, the Administrator has discretionary 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
authority whether to pay an award and to determine the amount of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
an award. The proposed regulation does not constrain this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
discretion. Although the proposed rule permits petitions for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
consideration for an award, whether an award is ultimately 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
granted will turn on the exercise of the Administrator
<!-- PJG 0034 unknown -->
s 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
unfettered discretion, including the application of factors 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
described in this proposed regulation. These factors include 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
whether the information or services constituted the initial, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
unsolicited notice of the violation to the government, whether 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the government would have obtained knowledge of the violation in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
a timely manner absent the information or services, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
importance of the case, the severity of the violation, the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
potential for or existence of actual or threatened harm to 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
persons or the environment, the willingness to assist in the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
government
<!-- PJG 0034 unknown -->
s enforcement action(s) regarding the violation(s), 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the value of the assistance in comparison to that given by any 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
other persons or sources of information or services and, in part, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the amount of money available to the EPA through appropriations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Furthermore, the rule is not intended to discourage self-auditing within facilities nor is it intended to encourage

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
concealment of information about violations or problems within a 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
facility by an employee from an employer. Thus, the regulation 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
sets forth the additional criterion of whether payment of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
award would improperly create incentives against the timely and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
appropriate identification of such a violation to either the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
employer or the government. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
G. Timing of Award Consideration 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
As mandated by section 113(f), persons may not be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
considered for an award unless and until such time as the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
information or services provided leads to a judicial or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
administrative civil penalty or a criminal conviction under 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
section 113 of the Act. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
H. Prepayment Offers 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The proposed regulation makes clear the distinction 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
between the Awards program and paid informant programs or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
contractual relationships that may be created by the Agency. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
EPA's employees do not have the authority under this proposal or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this statutory provision to promise that an award will be paid 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
nor to promise consideration or recommendation for an award. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
I. Request for Public Comment 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
The EPA is interested in public comment on all aspects of 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
this proposed rule. The EPA is particularly interested in 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
comments on: (1) The provision for confidentiality of identity 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for persons who provide information or services; (2) the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
eligibility exclusions and eligibility criteria for an award; (3) 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
petitions for consideration; and (4) the criteria for awards 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determinations. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=84 g=1 f=1 -->
III. Administrative Requirements 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
A. Executive Order 12866
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Under Executive Order 12866, (58 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
FR 51735 (October 4, 1993)) the Agency must 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determine whether the regulatory action is ``significant'' and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
therefore subject to OMB review and the requirements of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Executive Order. The Order defines ``significant regulatory 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
action'' as one that is likely to result in a rule that may: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1) Have an annual effect on the economy of $100 million or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
more or adversely affect in a material way the economy, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
productivity, competition, jobs, the environment, public health 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or safety, or State, local, or tribal governments or communities; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Create a serious inconsistency or otherwise interfere 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
with an action taken or planned by another agency; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) Materially alter the budgetary impact of entitlements, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
grants, user fees, or loan programs or the rights and obligations 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of recipients thereof; or 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) Raise novel legal or policy issues arising out of legal 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
mandates, the President's priorities, or the principles set forth 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
in the Executive Order. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Pursuant to the terms of Executive Order 12866, it has been 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
determined that this rule is a ``significant regulatory action''. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
As such, this action was submitted to OMB for review. Changes 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
made in response to OMB suggestions or recommendations will be 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
documented in public record. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
B. Regulatory Flexibility Act Compliance 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Pursuant to the provisions of 5 U.S.C. 605(b), I hereby certify 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
that this attached rule, if promulgated, will not have an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
economic impact on small entities because no additional costs 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
will be incurred. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=83 g=1 f=1 -->
C. Paperwork Reduction Act 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
Since this proposed rule does not create any new information 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
requirements or contain any new information collection 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
activities, no clearance is necessary from OMB under the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Paperwork Reduction Act of 1980, 44 U.S.C. 3501 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
et seq. 
