(f) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
EPA inspections.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 The inspections, reviews, collections, and audits under paragraph (b)(4) of this section may be conducted: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(1)(i) At the foreign refinery; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) At any other location where gasoline produced at the foreign refinery for use in the United States is stored or
transported; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(iii) At any other location where documents are kept which relate to the quality and/or quantity of the gasoline produced
at the foreign refinery for use in the United States; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Either announced in advance, or unannounced; 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) At any time prior to January 1, 2003; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) With relation to any gasoline produced: 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) During 1990 and any other year for which data are submitted to EPA in support of an individual baseline; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) For use in the United States during the period December 1994 through December 1997. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(g) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Failure to meet requirements.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 If any requirement specified in paragraphs (b) through (f) of this section is not fully met for any calendar year, or
if the Administrator determines that the information submitted to EPA under paragraphs (b) through (f) of this section
is inaccurate in whole or in part, then compliance with the requirements of &sect;&sect;80.41 (h) and (i) by an importer
shall be measured, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
ab initio
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 and for each and every calendar year or for such other period of time as the Administrator may determine, from the baseline
that otherwise would apply to the importer in the absence of the operation of this section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(h) 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
Volume constraints.
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
 (1) During any calendar year the total volume of gasoline imported by one or more importers to which a foreign refinery's
baseline applies shall not be greater than the refinery's 1990 baseline volume. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(2) Where the volume of gasoline for which the foreign refinery's baseline is claimed by one or more importers during
any calendar year exceeds the refinery's 1990 baseline volume, the refinery's baseline applies only to the first
volume of that refinery's gasoline that is imported into the United States that equals the 1990 baseline volume. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(3) In the event any importer uses a foreign refinery baseline in violation of the volume constraint specified in paragraphs
(h) (1) through (2) of this section the importer shall, 
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=3 -->
ab initio
<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
, calculate compliance using the baseline values that properly apply under paragraphs (h) (1) through (2) of this
section. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(4) In the event any gasoline is imported before January 1, 1995 for which a separate foreign refinery baseline is claimed:

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(i) Such gasoline shall be combined with gasoline imported during 1995 for which the separate foreign refinery baseline
is claimed for purposes of the volume constraint specified in paragraphs (h) (1) through (2) of this section; and 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
(ii) An adjusted 1990 baseline volume for the foreign refinery shall be calculated, for use during the combined 1994
and 1995 period only, by multiplying the 1990 baseline volume for the foreign refinery times 1.17. 
