<!-- PJG ITAG l=10 g=1 f=1 -->
Abstract: This action is needed to implement the 1994 Wool and Mohair 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Program, as required by legislation. The purpose of the Program 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is to encourage the continued domestic production of wool at 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
prices fair to both producers and consumers in a manner that will 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
assure a viable domestic wool industry in the future, by 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
supporting the prices of wool and mohair by means of loans, 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
purchases, payments, or other operations. The support level for 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
wool is set by statutory formula. Payments are to be 75 percent 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of the amount otherwise determined. The other determinations are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to: (1) support mohair at a level not more than 15 percent above 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
or below the comparable percentage of parity at which shorn wool 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
is supported, and (2) support pulled wool through payments based 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
on the liveweight of unshorn lambs marketed for slaughter. The 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
expected cost is $130&hyph;150 million. 
