<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
statutory formula, based on the Secretary's estimate of the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
amount of peanuts required for domestic food, seed, and related 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
uses for the 1995 marketing year. The 1995 marketing year is from 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
August 1, 1995, through July 31, 1996. 2) Minimum CCC 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
export-edible sales price for additional peanuts--established at 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the Secretary's discretion (the level has been set at $400 per 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
ton each of the last 7 years). The peanut program as a whole will 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
result in a net realized loss of about $46.5 million, which will 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
be attributable to loan forfeitures. 
